To see docker volumes

default location for docker volumes

/var/lib/docker/volumes

>> docker volumes ls

To create docker volumes

>> >> docker volume create [valume-name]

ex: >> docker volume create testvol

To see volume inspects

>> docker volume inspect testvol


Mounting a volume using -v or --mount 


>> docker run -it --name=[conainername] --mount source=[source-valume-name], destination=[destination-volume] centos

ex:

>> docker run -it --name=test01container --mount source=testvol, destination=/data centos

>> docker run -it --name=test02container -v testvol:/data centos 

Sharing volume between the containers
>> docker run -it --volumes-from test01container --name=test02container centos /bin/bash

Mounting a Host Directory as a data volume

>> mkdir files
>>  cd files
>> touch file.txt

>> docker run -it -name test03container -v "$(pwd)":/data1 centos

To remove docker volume

docker volume rm volumename
